SIMPLE: practitioner
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Practitioner
<hw>Prac*ti"tion*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Practician</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who is engaged in the
actual use or exercise of any art or profession, particularly that of
law or medicine.</def> <rj><au>Crabbe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who does anything customarily or
habitually.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A sly or artful person.</def>
<rj><au>Whitgift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>General practitioner</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>General</er>, 2.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Practive</ent>⟦br⟧
